HEADWORD: Fuliginous
<hw>Fu*lig"i*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fuliginosus</ets>, from <ets>fuligo</ets> soot: cf. F.
<ets>fuligineux</ets>. See <er>Fume</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to soot; sooty; dark; dusky.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to smoke; resembling smoke.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fuliginously</ent>⟦br⟧
